  "grammarPoint": {
    "title": "Люблю + infinitive, and a first look at plurals",
    "explanation": "**Люби́ть** (to love / like) is followed directly by an infinitive: **Я люблю́ чита́ть** — I like to read / I like reading. It conjugates a little unevenly — **люблю́, лю́бишь, лю́бит, лю́бим, лю́бите, лю́бят** — only the я-form has the extra л.\n\nMost nouns add **-ы** or **-и** for the plural: **фильм → фи́льмы** (film → films), **кни́га → кни́ги** (book → books, spelled with -и after г). You'll get the full pattern later — for now just recognize plurals when you see them.",
    "examples": [
      { "ru": "Я люблю́ чита́ть.", "en": "I like to read.", "note": "любить + infinitive" },
      { "ru": "Ты лю́бишь смотре́ть фи́льмы?", "en": "Do you like watching films?", "note": "фильм → фильмы, plural" },
      { "ru": "Мы лю́бим гуля́ть вме́сте.", "en": "We like walking together." },
      { "ru": "Она́ не лю́бит гото́вить.", "en": "She doesn't like cooking.", "note": "не + любит" }
    ]
  },

